<p>The Glow Protocol pairs three peptides that each approach tissue health from a different angle. GHK-Cu stimulates collagen production and shifts gene expression toward a younger pattern. BPC-157 drives angiogenesis and tissue repair at specific sites. TB-500 creates a systemic recovery environment that supports healing everywhere. Together, they cover the full spectrum from local repair to whole-body rejuvenation.</p>

<h2>What Each Peptide Contributes</h2>

<p><strong>GHK-Cu (copper peptide):</strong> The collagen driver. GHK-Cu upregulates synthesis of Type I and III collagen, elastin, and glycosaminoglycans. It also modulates over 4,000 genes, pushing expression patterns toward a younger profile. Applied topically, it improves skin texture, fine lines, and firmness. Injected systemically, it supports connective tissue health throughout the body and promotes hair growth through dermal papilla cell activation.</p>

<p><strong>BPC-157 (Body Protection Compound):</strong> The repair agent. BPC-157 accelerates healing through angiogenesis (new blood vessel formation) and fibroblast recruitment. In the context of skin health, increased blood supply and more active repair cells mean faster turnover and improved wound healing capacity. BPC-157 also reduces inflammation, which is relevant because chronic low-grade inflammation accelerates skin aging.</p>

<p><strong>TB-500 (Thymosin Beta-4):</strong> The systemic coordinator. TB-500 regulates actin dynamics to promote cell migration throughout the body. It reduces systemic inflammation and supports tissue remodeling. In the Glow Protocol, TB-500 provides the body-wide recovery support that allows GHK-Cu's collagen signals and BPC-157's local repair to work in an optimized environment.</p>

<h2>Standard Glow Protocol Dosing</h2>

<ul>
<li><strong>GHK-Cu:</strong> 1-2mg daily, subcutaneous injection. Additionally, topical GHK-Cu serum (1-3%) applied to face and neck daily.</li>
<li><strong>BPC-157:</strong> 250-500 mcg daily, subcutaneous injection.</li>
<li><strong>TB-500:</strong> 2-2.5mg twice weekly (loading phase for first 4 weeks), then 2mg once weekly (maintenance).</li>
<li><strong>Cycle length:</strong> 8-12 weeks. Many users run the protocol once or twice per year.</li>
</ul>

<p>All three injectable peptides can be drawn into the same syringe for a single daily injection (combining the daily GHK-Cu and BPC-157 doses with the TB-500 dose on TB-500 days). The topical GHK-Cu is applied separately.</p>

